This paper deals with the analysis of algorithms for solving discounted Markov decision processes and turn-based stochastic games, which are topics related to game theory, optimization, and artificial intelligence. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), followed by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
